div.div: A system that can self-modify is one that can inject variance in its components as needed. In this case the system is too static/inflexible to adapt and needs points where changes have a point of entry to the system, either by being generated from variance gaps inside the system, or injected from outside the system. An example would be a language function with a change interface or an error-generator with a change interface to adapt the language between primary sub-systems.
